description.p:
The purpose of the present invention can be achieved with the following methods.
(1) A method for replenishing developing fluid in an automatic developing apparatus for photosensitive materials, comprising the steps of:
a) replenishing the developing fluid based on a first predetermined replenishing condition to compensate for the reduction of developing activity of the developing fluid over time due to its reaction with atmospheric carbon dioxide;
b) replenishing the developing fluid based on a second predetermined replenishing condition to compensate for the reduction of the activity of the developing fluid caused by the processing of photosensitive materials;
c) measuring the electric conductivity of the replenished developing fluid;
d) calculating a replenisher replacement ratio which reflects the extent to which the developing fluid is replaced by at least one of the replenishing fluid and a diluent for reducing the electric conductivity of the developing fluid; and
e) supplying a diluent to the developing fluid until the electric conductivity of the developing fluid falls below an electric conductivity target value calculated from the replenisher replacement ratio if the measured value of the electric conductivity of the developer exceeds the electric conductivity target value.
(2) A method according to (1), wherein the electric conductivity target value is calculated from the replenisher replacement ratio and either:
a) a dilution ratio which is the sum of the volume of diluent used for diluting the replenishing fluid and the volume of diluent supplied to the developer tank in order to lower the electric conductivity of the developing fluid, with respect to the volume of the replenishing fluid; or
b) a ratio of the integral amount of the replenishing fluid which is supplied to the developer tank to compensate for the reduction of the developing activity of the developing fluid due to its reaction with atmospheric carbon dioxide over time, with respect to the product of the replenisher replacement ratio and the volume of the developer.
